/*******************************************************************
The open source code from github:
TextConcord.java

Execution:
1. unzip TextConcord-master.zip
2. cd TextConcord-master/src/concord
3. javac TextConcord.java
4. cd TextConcord-master/src/
5. java concord/TextConcord ../test
6. the results are stored in concord.*.out in /src/

Functionality:
1. parse files in a given directory
2. read every word in the files
3. count the frequency of the words
4. rank the words according to the frequency and alphabetical order
5. output the words in a file

/******************************************************************
The code after translation:
TextConcord.cpp

Execution:
1.  g++ TextConcord.cpp -o TextConcord
2. ./TextConcord test/
3. the results are stored in concord.*.out in the current path

